defs.value: pub fn slice(&str, isize, isize) -> String
defs.docs: Extracts from `subject` a string from `start` position up to `end` position. The character at `end` position is not included.

attributes.value: / Extracts from `subject` a string from `start` position up to `end` position. The character at `end` position is not included.
/ * `start` - The position to start extraction. 0 means extract from the beginning of the `subject`. If negative use `subject.len() + start`.
/ * `end` - The position to end extraction. 0 means extract to the end of the `subject`. If negative use `subject.len() + end`.
